🟦 US mise à jour — Determine eligibility for Request creation

US1 — Determine eligibility for Request creation (via HAM, OPAL hierarchy and SharePoint rules)

As a system
I want to determine whether a return or allocation is eligible for Request creation
So that backend processing follows Group Catalog rules dynamically

⸻

Description

For each equipment:

🔹 Step 1 — Identify business and country
	•	If equipment is found in HAM:
	•	Retrieve:
	•	Owner OU (business entity)
	•	Location Country
	•	If equipment is not found in HAM:
	•	Use:
	•	Visitor’s business entity
	•	Visitor’s country

⸻

🔹 Step 2 — Match with SharePoint eligibility list
	•	Search for a matching row in SharePoint:
	•	(Owner OU + Country)

⸻

🔹 Step 3 — Handle Owner OU hierarchy (OPAL)

If no match is found:
	•	Use OPAL hierarchy:
	•	Retrieve parent Owner OU
	•	Retry matching (Parent OU + Country)
	•	Repeat until:
	•	a match is found
	•	OR top of hierarchy is reached

⸻

🔹 Step 4 — Evaluate eligibility conditions

If a matching row is found:
	•	Check:
	•	catalogs supported = yes
	•	AND depending on equipment type:
	•	HAM Workstation = yes
	•	OR HAM Mobile = yes

⸻

🔹 Final decision
	•	If all conditions are met → RequestAllowed = true
	•	Otherwise → RequestAllowed = false

⸻

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN an equipment is processed
WHEN eligibility is evaluated
THEN Owner OU and Country are determined

IF equipment is found in HAM
THEN Owner OU and Location Country are retrieved from HAM

IF equipment is not found in HAM
THEN Visitor entity and country are used

WHEN no match is found in SharePoint
THEN the system traverses the Owner OU hierarchy (OPAL)
UNTIL a match is found OR root is reached

IF no match is found after hierarchy traversal
THEN RequestAllowed = false

IF a match is found
AND catalogs supported = yes
AND (HAM Workstation = yes OR HAM Mobile = yes depending on equipment)
THEN RequestAllowed = true

IN ALL OTHER CASES
THEN RequestAllowed = false


